  <section id="alard-meaning" class="alard-meaning">
    <div class="am-grid">
      <!-- Block 1: Text Left -->
      <div class="am-text am-bg-gold">
        <div class="am-inner">
          <div class="am-image show-mobile">
            <img
              src="{{'mean.png'|asset_img_url:'original'}}"
              alt="Palestinian woman harvesting wheat"
            >
          </div>

          <h2>Al’Ard Means “The Land”</h2>

          <p>
            As the biggest olive oil producer in Palestine, Al’Ard is proud to carry the responsibility of sharing this
            heritage with the world. Our farmers, groves, and facilities make us uniquely able to guarantee
            authenticity, quality, and scale, without ever compromising tradition.
          </p>
          <p>
            This season is full of challenges, but together we can ensure that the story of resilience, and the finest
            olive oil of Palestine, reaches your table.
          </p>
          <p class="am-highlight">Buy ethically. Support Palestinian farmers.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Block 2: Image Right -->
      <div class="am-image hide-mobile">
        <img
          src="{{'mean.png'|asset_img_url:'original'}}"
          alt="Palestinian woman harvesting wheat"
        >
      </div>

      <!-- Block 3: Image Left -->
      <div class="am-image hide-mobile">
        <img
          src="{{'mean2.png'|asset_img_url:'original'}}"
          alt="Palestinian farmer planting olive tree"
        >
      </div>

      <!-- Block 4: Text Right -->
      <div class="am-text am-bg-brown">
        <div class="am-inner">
          <div class="am-image show-mobile">
            <img
              src="{{'mean2.png'|asset_img_url:'original'}}"
              alt="Palestinian woman harvesting wheat"
            >
          </div>

          <h2>What Does The Olive Tree Mean To Palestinians?</h2>

          <p>
            For Palestinians, the olive tree is far more than a crop, it is a living symbol of heritage, resilience, and
            identity. Rooted in the land for thousands of years, it connects generations through family groves passed
            down over time, while sustaining entire communities through the harvest and production of olive oil.
          </p>
          <p>
            Each season, families and neighbors come together to pick the olives, turning the harvest into a shared
            cultural and social ritual. Deeply tied to faith and tradition, the olive tree also represents peace,
            blessing, and steadfastness, standing strong in the face of hardship just as Palestinians have done for
            generations.
          </p>
          <p>
            At Al’Ard, we honor this legacy by bringing the fruit of these ancient trees from our farmers in Palestine
            to homes around the world, sharing not only the richness of the oil but also the story of resilience and
            rootedness it carries.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

